aggregate.name: st_3dextent
aggregate.Comment: args: geomfield - an aggregate function that returns the box3D bounding box that bounds rows of geometries.

aggregate.name: st_accum
aggregate.Comment: args: geomfield - Aggregate. Constructs an array of geometries.

aggregate.name: st_clusterintersecting
aggregate.Comment: args: g - Aggregate. Returns an array with the connected components of a set of geometries

aggregate.name: st_clusterwithin
aggregate.Comment: args: g, distance - Aggregate. Returns an array of GeometryCollections, where each GeometryCollection represents a set of geometries separated by no more than the specified distance.

aggregate.name: st_collect
aggregate.Comment: args: g1field - Return a specified ST_Geometry value from a collection of other geometries.

aggregate.name: st_countagg
aggregate.Comment: args: rast, exclude_nodata_value - Aggregate. Returns the number of pixels in a given band of a set of rasters. If no band is specified defaults to band 1. If exclude_nodata_value is set to true, will only count pixels that are not equal to the NODATA value.

aggregate.name: st_countagg
aggregate.Comment: args: rast, nband, exclude_nodata_value - Aggregate. Returns the number of pixels in a given band of a set of rasters. If no band is specified defaults to band 1. If exclude_nodata_value is set to true, will only count pixels that are not equal to the NODATA value.

aggregate.name: st_countagg
aggregate.Comment: args: rast, nband, exclude_nodata_value, sample_percent - Aggregate. Returns the number of pixels in a given band of a set of rasters. If no band is specified defaults to band 1. If exclude_nodata_value is set to true, will only count pixels that are not equal to the NODATA value.

aggregate.name: st_extent
aggregate.Comment: args: geomfield - an aggregate function that returns the bounding box that bounds rows of geometries.

aggregate.name: st_makeline
aggregate.Comment: args: geoms - Creates a Linestring from point or line geometries.

aggregate.name: st_memunion
aggregate.Comment: args: geomfield - Same as ST_Union, only memory-friendly (uses less memory and more processor time).

aggregate.name: st_polygonize
aggregate.Comment: args: geomfield - Aggregate. Creates a GeometryCollection containing possible polygons formed from the constituent linework of a set of geometries.

aggregate.name: st_samealignment
aggregate.Comment: args: rastfield - Returns true if rasters have same skew, scale, spatial ref, and offset (pixels can be put on same grid without cutting into pixels) and false if they dont with notice detailing issue.

aggregate.name: st_summarystatsagg
aggregate.Comment: args: rast, exclude_nodata_value, sample_percent - Aggregate. Returns summarystats consisting of count, sum, mean, stddev, min, max for a given raster band of a set of raster. Band 1 is assumed is no band is specified.

aggregate.name: st_summarystatsagg
aggregate.Comment: args: rast, nband, exclude_nodata_value - Aggregate. Returns summarystats consisting of count, sum, mean, stddev, min, max for a given raster band of a set of raster. Band 1 is assumed is no band is specified.

aggregate.name: st_summarystatsagg
aggregate.Comment: args: rast, nband, exclude_nodata_value, sample_percent - Aggregate. Returns summarystats consisting of count, sum, mean, stddev, min, max for a given raster band of a set of raster. Band 1 is assumed is no band is specified.

aggregate.name: st_union
aggregate.Comment: args: g1field - Returns a geometry that represents the point set union of the Geometries.

object-type.name: addbandarg
object-type.Comment: postgis raster type: A composite type used as input into the ST_AddBand function defining the attributes and initial value of the new band.

object-type.name: box2d
object-type.Comment: postgis type: A box composed of x min, ymin, xmax, ymax. Often used to return the 2d enclosing box of a geometry.

object-type.name: box3d
object-type.Comment: postgis type: A box composed of x min, ymin, zmin, xmax, ymax, zmax. Often used to return the 3d extent of a geometry or collection of geometries.

object-type.name: geography
object-type.Comment: postgis type: Ellipsoidal spatial data type.

object-type.name: geometry
object-type.Comment: postgis type: Planar spatial data type.

object-type.name: geometry_dump
object-type.Comment: postgis type: A spatial datatype with two fields - geom (holding a geometry object) and path[] (a 1-d array holding the position of the geometry within the dumped object.)

object-type.name: geomval
object-type.Comment: postgis raster type: A spatial datatype with two fields - geom (holding a geometry object) and val (holding a double precision pixel value from a raster band).

object-type.name: rastbandarg
object-type.Comment: postgis raster type: A composite type for use when needing to express a raster and a band index of that raster.

object-type.name: raster
object-type.Comment: postgis raster type: raster spatial data type.

object-type.name: reclassarg
object-type.Comment: postgis raster type: A composite type used as input into the ST_Reclass function defining the behavior of reclassification.

object-type.name: summarystats
object-type.Comment: postgis raster type: A composite type returned by the ST_SummaryStats and ST_SummaryStatsAgg functions.

object-type.name: unionarg
object-type.Comment: postgis raster type: A composite type used as input into the ST_Union function defining the bands to be processed and behavior of the UNION operation.
